# Motion Keypoint Trajectory and Covariance Descriptor for Human Action Recognition

## Prerequisites
(1)OpenCV library (V2.4.6)
(2)ffmpeg library (V2.4.2)

## Compilation
The basic steps of compiling the code are as follows:

mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
make

## License
Copyright (C) 2017 Multimedia and Intelligent Computing Lab. 

The code is the implementation of MKT and TBC [1]. In this implementation, we utilized some functions from the code of [2] and [3]. Please cite the following papers if you use this code. 

[1]Yun Yi and Hanli Wang, Motion Keypoint Trajectory and Covariance Descriptor for Human Action Recognition, The Visual Computer, in press, 2017. 
[2]Heng Wang and Cordelia Schmid, Action Recognition with Improved Trajectories, IEEE International Conference on Computer Vision, 2013.
[3]Jiayi Ma, Ji Zhao, Jinwen Tian, Alan Yuille, and Zhuowen Tu, Robust Point Matching via Vector Field Consensus, IEEE Transactions on Image Processing, 23(4), pp. 1706-1721, 2014.
